    <main>
        <h1>LeetCode 762: Prime Number of Set Bits in Binary Representation (C++)</h1>

        <div class="problem-description">
            <p><strong>Problem:</strong>
                Given two integers left and right, return the count of numbers in the inclusive range [left, right] having a prime number of set bits in their binary representation. Recall that the number of set bits an integer has is the number of 1's present when written in binary. For example, 21 written in binary is 10101, which has 3 set bits.
            </p>
            <p><strong>Example:</strong>
                Input: left = 6, right = 10<br/>
                Output: 4<br/>
                Explanation: 6  -&gt; 110 (2 set bits, 2 is prime)<br/>
                7  -&gt; 111 (3 set bits, 3 is prime)<br/>
                8  -&gt; 1000 (1 set bit, 1 is not prime)<br/>
                9  -&gt; 1001 (2 set bits, 2 is prime)<br/>
                10 -&gt; 1010 (2 set bits, 2 is prime)<br/>
                4 numbers have a prime number of set bits.<br/><br/>
                Input: left = 10, right = 15<br/>
                Output: 5<br/>
                Explanation: 10 -&gt; 1010 (2 set bits, 2 is prime)<br/>
                11 -&gt; 1011 (3 set bits, 3 is prime)<br/>
                12 -&gt; 1100 (2 set bits, 2 is prime)<br/>
                13 -&gt; 1101 (3 set bits, 3 is prime)<br/>
                14 -&gt; 1110 (3 set bits, 3 is prime)<br/>
                15 -&gt; 1111 (4 set bits, 4 is not prime)<br/>
                5 numbers have a prime number of set bits.
            </p>
        </div>

        <div class="code-container">
            <button class="copy-button" onclick="copyCode(this)">Copy Code</button>
            <pre><code class="language-cpp">class Solution {
public:
    int countPrimeSetBits(int left, int right) {
        // Primes up to 20 (since max number of bits in 10^6 is ~20)
        unordered_set&lt;int&gt; primes = {2, 3, 5, 7, 11, 13, 17, 19};
        int count = 0;
        
        for (int num = left; num &lt;= right; num++) {
            int setBits = __builtin_popcount(num);
            if (primes.count(setBits)) {
                count++;
            }
        }
        
        return count;
    }
};</code></pre>
